(57) Abstract: The invention relates to a bicycle adjust
ing device, particularly an adjusting device for adjusting
the height ofthe front wheel suspension, of the rear wheel
suspension, of the seat or of the handlebar fore-part of a
bicycle, e.g. of a mountain bike. The invention also re
lates to a bicycle equipped with at least one bicycle ad
justing device and to a bicycle steering head bearing sys
tem. The adjusting device comprises a double-action pis
ton/cylinder assembly having a first cylinder space (14a,
34a) and a second cylinder space (15a, 35a), and both
one another via a fluid channel (16a, 16b, 12a, 12b).
